- Keep documents concrete, restrained, and implementation-guiding.
- Avoid marketing language and broad claims without evidence.
- Prefer updating canonical docs over adding scratch planning files.
- When documenting a tradeoff, state what was chosen, why, and what remains uncertain.
- Ensure docs help future agents make narrower and better decisions.
